ygData.subject: RE: [eqbards] In a rut at 40
ygData.msgSnippet: Many of them don t, but I think the new damage table (now same as warriors does). Jarroll mentioned that he was doing much better soloing last night too ...
ygData.messageBody:
Many of them don't, but I think the new damage table (now same as warriors
does). Jarroll mentioned that he was doing much better soloing last night
too

--- "Kimes, Dean W." <dean_kimes@...> wrote:

<HR>
<html><body>
<tt>
Do the new melee changes affect things pre-50?  If so maybe I need to
dust<BR>
off Kitasi and see how he fares now.<BR>
<BR>
-----Original Message-----<BR>
From: John Grady [mailto:john_grady@...]<BR>
Sent: Tuesday, October 09, 2001 2:33 PM<BR>
To: eqbards@yahoogroups.com<BR>
Subject: Re: [eqbards] In a rut at 40<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
I would try fear kiting in DL and see if the new melee changes make that
a<BR>
more viable option now. Jonathon's, Snare and Fear.<BR>
<BR>
Tz<BR>
<BR>
--- Christopher Sanders <christopher.sanders@...>
wrote:<BR>
<BR>
<HR><BR>
<html><body><BR>
<tt><BR>
Ok, I've been 40 for about a month now, and have 2 bubbles to
go. <BR>
I'm sick<BR><BR>
of being 40!!<BR><BR>
<BR><BR>
I'm also sick of pickup groups!  Heh.  So, any advice
would be<BR>
welcome on<BR><BR>
where to go at this level, and what song combination to use to solo me<BR>
2<BR><BR>
bubbles as quickly as possible.<BR><BR>
<BR><BR>
I've been using chains-fulfils-tuyens, but it takes so long to kill a<BR>
frost<BR><BR>
giant this way...I get bored quickly (hence, 40 for a
month...hehe).<BR><BR>
<BR><BR>
Thank you!<BR><BR>
Atonal<BR><BR>
</tt><BR>
<BR>
<br><BR>
<BR>
